{
  "texts": [
    "The key limitation of leveraging LLMs in industrial recommender systems is efficiency [63,156,185], including considerations of both time and space.",
    "On the one hand, the fine-tuning and inference efficiency of LLMs cannot compare to traditional recommendation models [44,186].",
    "While techniques such as parameterefficient fine-tuning can aid in keeping LLMs updated in a computationally efficient manner, recommender systems need to iterate continuously over time, i.e., incremental learning.",
    "Frequent updates of LLMs inevitably bring spatial and temporal burdens to recommender systems [121].",
    "On the other hand, billions of parameters in LLMs also pose challenges for the lightweight deployment of recommendation algorithms [131,132]."
  ]
}